        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
San Pablo, or 31 miles southeast of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Luis, Mesita, Jaroso, San Acacio, San Pablo, Fort Garland,
Sanchez Reservoir, Chama, and Garcia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
